    <div style="basic">
        <p begin="00:00:00.000" end="00:00:03.600" tts:direction="ltr">All right. As we jump into querying
<br />multiple tables,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:03.600" end="00:00:10.160" tts:direction="ltr">here is a good slide to reflect on the
<br />format of how to query multiple tables.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:10.160" end="00:00:14.960" tts:direction="ltr">We select the different columns that we
<br />would like to see.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:14.960" end="00:00:19.480" tts:direction="ltr">We do not necessarily have to use the
<br />table aliases,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:19.480" end="00:00:22.600" tts:direction="ltr">but we can, especially with ambiguous
<br />column names,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:22.600" end="00:00:25.720" tts:direction="ltr">we must use them with ambiguous column
<br />names.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:25.720" end="00:00:28.760" tts:direction="ltr">When we query, we will have</p>
        <p begin="00:00:28.760" end="00:00:32.120" tts:direction="ltr">from table one listed here, and then on
<br />the next line,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:32.120" end="00:00:36.240" tts:direction="ltr">we will add our join keyword and then list
<br />table two</p>
        <p begin="00:00:36.240" end="00:00:41.440" tts:direction="ltr">and the on matching columns will be set
<br />equal to each other.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:41.440" end="00:00:43.760" tts:direction="ltr">As we are querying multiple tables,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:43.760" end="00:00:46.240" tts:direction="ltr">we must continually be questioning what</p>
        <p begin="00:00:46.240" end="00:00:50.000" tts:direction="ltr">does each record represent in our output.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:50.000" end="00:00:52.640" tts:direction="ltr">Let's take one more look at this.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:52.640" end="00:00:57.360" tts:direction="ltr">Let's see here that the overall general
<br />idea of multable queries is that I</p>
        <p begin="00:00:57.360" end="00:01:01.960" tts:direction="ltr">want to see data from two different
